  stimulus_text = 'The first time that humans walked on the Moon, it was a monumental event. The mission, which was led by the United States, had been years in the making. The world watched with bated breath as the astronauts Neil Armstrong and Buzz Aldrin, took their first steps on the lunar surface. After returning to Earth, the astronauts were hailed as heroes, and their journey inspired generations of scientists and engineers. What does this passage suggest about how the astronauts felt after returning to Earth?',
